# bitHuman Swift SDK — minimal example
# Copy this file: cp .env.example .env

# ── Required: path to a packed .imx model ──────────────────────
# Build one with the Python SDK's `bithuman pack` CLI — see
# README.md § "1. Build the .imx model". The example falls
# back to the first CLI argument or the conventional cache
# location if this var is unset.
# BITHUMAN_MODEL_PATH=/path/to/expression.imx

# ── Optional: API secret for metered billing ──────────────────
# Get from https://www.bithuman.ai → Developer → API Keys.
# Only needed if the example is modified to call
# `Bithuman.create(modelPath:apiSecret:)` (the metered variant).
# Out-of-the-box the example runs unmetered.
# BITHUMAN_API_SECRET=
